<p align="center"><font face="Arial" size="2">“If you learn only Kung Fu form but never develop Kung Fu force,<br> your Kung Fu will be futile even if you study for the rest of your life.” --- Wong Kiew Kit</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uraystonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raystonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/3/02 8:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixing wizards: my recommendations (long)</span><hr size=1> Your post is great.  However, I have one observation.  None of this actually takes into account how much damage is being absorbed by the Tanks.  Tanks have an outrageously useful ability at taking damage without flinching.  Most of the time their extremely high AC evades and absorbs the hits.  If they get low on health they can get their wounds bound up to half health very cheap (something we cannot do with our mana.)  This ability to absorb damage should not be given to them for free.  If you keep the average damage per second equal among all classes and allow tanks to have this ability to absorb damage for free, then everything becomes unbalanced in favor of melees.<br>
<br>
In constrast to what many think, melees are not supposed to have the best damage over time figures.  They are supposed to have the best damage-evade-and-absorb figures.  Their main use is not to deal out damage, but to protect others in the group while these others do the damage.  Imagine how much more useful Wizards would be in an xp grind group if tanks could stand their all day getting pounded on, but only did tiny amounts of damage.  They could kill most anything alone but it would take a couple years to do it.  This is how the game should be balanced.  Tanks should be absorbing damage and should rely on others to inflict 90% of it.  Wizards should be inflicting damage and should rely on others to absorb 90% of it.<br>
<br>
-Raystonn<br>
