<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Rogues, Monks, and Rangers are not TANKS. by any stretch of the imagination. They are there for long term damage output.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I agree here.  Rogues and monks should be able to do a great deal of damage to non-magical creatures.  Magical creatures should be the realm of casters however.  Rangers should get special bonuses that allow them to do extra damage, hide, sneak, move quickly, etc. when in outdoor zones.  They should be weak warriors when fighting in indoor zones.  They are rangers after all.  Their specialty is the wilderness.<br>
<br>
-Raystonn<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<br>Need a log parsed?</span><br>  Posts: 608<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/3/02 9:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixing wizards: my recommendations (long)</span><hr size=1> A couple thoughts and responses:<br>
<br>
First, I should note that even if Verant does the unthinkable and implements all of my suggestions verbatim, and 400 wizards sign off on it, it will prevent some wizards from being unsatisfied with their lot in life. Some believe that mana should outdamage melee in all circumstances. I should make it clear that my goal is not to make wizards happy, but to provide a more level playing field (ie: balance) which will encourage wizard grouping.  Note that this point is not directed at any particular individual. Honest!<br>
<br>
Grimstaff:<br>
Good to see you again! I haven't read a post from you in a while... maybe I've just been looking in the wrong places.<br>
<br>
Saradin:<br>
Thanks for the encouragement and the comments. Perhaps &quot;stupid&quot; is too strong a word. Perhaps I should substitute &quot;gay!&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  The &quot;well, duh&quot; comment makes a bit more sense if you run the robe through the spreadsheet, where you'll find that it *reduces* wizard damage output. A wizard will do better meditating and nuking than trying to use this POS. Every wizard knows this, whether they have the robe or not. Even so, I'll take your comments under advisement, and will likely make a change <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Also... for the twink issue.  It is trivial for saavy melee characters to acquire decent gear without any foreign cash infusion. I started a new ranger on another server to play with some newbie friends. By level 6, by harvesting and selling bat wings and bone chips, I had earned enough to by a Frozen Longsword (7/27) from another player. This is not godlike, by any stretch, but for a level 6, it roughly doubled my damage output from rusty. There simply is *no* wizard equivalent to this.<br>
<br>
Raystonn:<br>
Actually, in the FAQ I did touch on the value of melee tanking ability. My contention is that melee tanking ability is roughly as valuable as the wizard's utility spells (snare, evac, stun). Some will say more, some will say less, but calling it a wash sure makes the comparisons easier. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uetnu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>etnu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1104<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/3/02 9:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixing wizards: my recommendations (long)</span><hr size=1> No, utility vs. tankage is a fine balance. If you give warriors our utility then you break down class differences even further.<br>
<br>
By utility, I was referring specifically to:<br>
<br>
Snare<br>
Stun<br>
Root<br>
any other combat &quot;utility&quot;<br>
<br>
Not ports, not translocates, etc.<br>
<br>
<br>
As for new servers: While Lammy's and fungi tunics won't be in the game on twinks for several months, NEITHER WOULD THE NEW ITEMS!<br>
<br>
The vermillion orb wouldn't be held by a level 20 wizard, nor would the lammy be held by a level 20 warrior.<br>
<br>
As the server matures, and that level 20 wizard got to level 60 and had himself a VP robe or whatever, that warrior would be level 60 with primal and whatnot.<br>
<br>
Then the level 20 warriors would have lammy's while level 20 wizards had vermillion orbs.<br>
<br>
Seems perfectly reasonable to me.... <p>Etnu Phyresoul, serving Solusek Ro since March 2000.
<BR>
"Wait, I suggest you go play a druid, the class Verant invented so that even retards could play" </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<br>Err, Forum Arch Mage?</span><br>  Posts: 899<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/3/02 9:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixing wizards: my recommendations (long)</span><hr size=1> Wow excellent summary.<br>
<br>
My first suggestion would be to make clear somewhere the point that this is wizards as a damage dealer.  Perhaps at the start you could say something like:<br>
<br>
Assuming that the pure defensive needs of a group are covered; such as, but not limited to, the common foundation of cleric, warrior, and enchanter; we can compare the overall damage dealing ability of a wizard to the overall damage dealing ability of a melee without worrying about secondary abilities.<br>
<br>
{Edit: Utility can be included here, but I think the FAQ adequetely addressed the direct comparison of utility to tankage}<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Note that full burn damage could use some adjustment as well, given that full burn rate for a wizard at 60 is 150 dps,<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  h) Ah that reminds me. Wizards are the best at *fast damage*. Does your model account for that?<br>
Well, no. I do have two point to make on this however: First, melee weapons have advanced to the point where they are able to achieve 50% or better of the damage rate of a wizard on full burn, which means 2 tanks will &quot;burn down&quot; a mob as well or better than a wizard. Second, the value of this skill is really reduced by the mezmerize skill. Burning down adds with fast damage or AE would seem to be the obvious case where variable damage is needed, but when you are engaging mobs one at a time, the difference in the damage rate becomes a much less useful skill. Make this skill more useful in more circumstances, then we can talk.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I am curious how you came up with the full burn numbers listed above, and whether aggro was taken into consideration.  The number appears accurate to me, but ask because as a 55 mage completely ignoring aggro, I've managed to get as high as 180dps in 9 seconds with rains+nukes+pet on a level 40 mob.  In normal situations, the number is considerably lower because 180dps start to finish on an xp group mob is almost always going to draw aggro.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  l) Won't this make wizards even better in raids, where they don't need any help?<br>
Well, yes. I haven't done a full analysis on this, but preliminary analysis has seemed to indicate that while wizards do very well against boss mobs currently, the performance gap is not as great as most believe.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I also might mention that the right click nukes would have little effect on boss mob encounters except for absurdly long fights.  This would also make wizards feel a little less useless when they empty their mana into a mob that manages to channel complete heal anyway.  Also, I would note that already, the primary limiting factor on raids is aggro, not mana.<br>
<br>
Also, sorry if this isn't considered &quot;constructive&quot; criticism, but I would run this through a spell checker before sending it anywhere.  There aren't too many mistakes, but I think there were enough to be a little distracting.<br>
<br>
